{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"70d9c6c7-c094-41ea-a701-0f6e0aa31abf","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IDisposable, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected automatically via constructor in MSTest 3.x\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; } \n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // For async initialization, implement IAsyncInitializable or use [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test initialization\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n\n    // Sync cleanup\n    public void Dispose() { }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() \n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n- **TestContext injection** — pass it via the constructor (no more `[TestContext]` property setter needed).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` (runs before each test) or `[ClassInitialize]` for one-time class-level setup.\n- **Cleanup** — implement `IDisposable` / `IAsyncDisposable` for per-test teardown, or use `[TestCleanup]` / `[ClassCleanup]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0065d35b-a8d1-405b-85ba-60844f8f5e2b","outputTokens":407,"requestId":"BC27:A067E:1C1B77E:1F5D552:69FA9725"},"id":"723cb923-0413-4826-ad60-cc3e21b786ca","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:19:43.004Z","parentId":"e3d841d4-3156-4756-9cec-c7ecee157b50"}
